\begin_inset Formula 
\[
EX_{t}=2p_{0}-1,
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Var\,X_{t}=4p_{0}(1-p_{0}).
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For the expected value and variance of the transition probability or the
 
\begin_inset Formula $t\ge1$
\end_inset

 iteration of the walk 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{t}$
\end_inset

 it holds AMISTAT
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
EP_{t}=p_{0},
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Var\,P_{t}=(2\lambda-\lambda^{2})^{t}p_{0}^{2}+p_{0}(1-\lambda)^{2}\sum_{i=0}^{t-1}(2\lambda-\lambda^{2})^{i}-p_{0}^{2}.
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Finally, the expected position of the walker 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{t}$
\end_inset

 after 
\begin_inset Formula $t\geq1$
\end_inset

 iterations can be expressed as AMISTAT
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
ES_{t}=S_{0}+t(2p_{0}-1).
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

